article.headline: Bucknell 72, Lehigh 51
article.story: LEWISBURG, Pa. -- Patrick Behan scored 23 points and had nine rebounds to lead Bucknell to a 72-51 victory over Lehigh on Wednesday night. Bryan Cohen scored 17 points and Justin Castleberry had 13 for Bucknell (7-21, 4-9 Patriot League), which held a 31-15 lead at the half. Zahir Carrington had 15 points and 12 rebounds to lead Lehigh (15-12, 5-8), while Marquis Hall scored 11 points and Rob Keefer had 10. Bucknell shot 47.3 percent for the game, including 50 percent in the second half, and made 10 of 11 free throws. Lehigh managed only 31.7 percent for the game, including 17.2 percent in the first half, and got no closer than 13 points in the second half.
